# Uptime Kuma Setup Guide

## Access
- URL: `https://status.{{ target_domain }}`
- First-time setup: Create admin account on initial login

## Recommended Monitors
Add these HTTP/HTTPS monitors after deployment:

| Service | URL | Check Interval |
|---------|-----|----------------|
| Traefik | `https://traefik.{{ target_domain }}` | 60s |
| Grafana | `https://grafana.{{ target_domain }}/api/health` | 60s |
| Netdata | `http://{{ target_control_ip }}:19999/api/v1/info` | 60s |
| Pi-hole | `http://{{ target_control_ip }}:{{ control_dns.pihole_port }}/admin` | 60s |
| Authentik | `https://auth.{{ target_domain }}/-/health/live/` | 60s |
| Loki | `http://{{ target_control_ip }}:{{ control_loki.port }}/ready` | 60s |

## Docker Monitors
Use Docker container monitoring for local services:
- Type: Docker Container
- Container Name: e.g., `grafana`, `traefik`, `loki`

## Push Monitors
Configure push URLs in vault for external monitoring:
- `vault_uptime_kuma_push_urls.system` — System health
- `vault_uptime_kuma_push_urls.backup` — Backup completion
